119/**
120 * @brief CreateEmptyFile create minimal empty file.
121 */
122void VPattern::CreateEmptyFile()
123{
124 this->clear();
125 QDomElement patternElement = this->createElement(TagPattern);
126
127 patternElement.appendChild(createComment(FileComment()));
128
129 QDomElement version = createElement(TagVersion);
130 QDomText newNodeText = createTextNode(VPatternConverter::PatternMaxVerStr);
131 version.appendChild(newNodeText);
132 patternElement.appendChild(version);
133
134 QDomElement unit = createElement(TagUnit);
135 newNodeText = createTextNode(UnitsToStr(qApp->patternUnit()));
136 unit.appendChild(newNodeText);
137 patternElement.appendChild(unit);
138
139 patternElement.appendChild(createElement(TagDescription));
140 patternElement.appendChild(createElement(TagNotes));
141
142 patternElement.appendChild(createElement(TagMeasurements));
143 patternElement.appendChild(createElement(TagVariables));
144
145 this->appendChild(patternElement);
146 insertBefore(createProcessingInstruction("xml", "version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\""), this->firstChild());
147}

157/**
158 * @brief Parse parse file.
159 * @param parse parser file mode.
160 */
161void VPattern::Parse(const Document &parse)
162{
163 qCDebug(vXML, "Parsing pattern.");
164 switch (parse)
165 {
166 case Document::FullParse:
167 qCDebug(vXML, "Full parse.");
168 break;
169 case Document::LiteParse:
170 qCDebug(vXML, "Lite parse.");
171 break;
172 case Document::LiteBlockParse:
173 qCDebug(vXML, "Lite draft block parse.");
174 break;
175 default:
176 break;
177 }
178
179 SCASSERT(draftScene != nullptr)
180 SCASSERT(pieceScene != nullptr)
181 QStringList tags = QStringList() << TagDraftBlock << TagVariables << TagDescription << TagNotes
182 << TagMeasurements << TagVersion << TagGradation << TagImage << TagUnit
183 << TagPatternName << TagPatternNum << TagCompanyName << TagCustomerName
184 << TagPatternLabel;
185 PrepareForParse(parse);
186 QDomNode domNode = documentElement().firstChild();
187 while (domNode.isNull() == false)
188 {
189 if (domNode.isElement())
190 {
191 const QDomElement domElement = domNode.toElement();
192 if (domElement.isNull() == false)
193 {
194 switch (tags.indexOf(domElement.tagName()))
195 {
196 case 0: // TagDraftBlock
197 qCDebug(vXML, "Tag draw.");
198 if (parse == Document::FullParse)
199 {
200 if (activeDraftBlock.isEmpty())
201 {
202 setActiveDraftBlock(GetParametrString(domElement, AttrName));
203 }
204 else
205 {
206 changeActiveDraftBlock(GetParametrString(domElement, AttrName));
207 }
208 patternPieces << GetParametrString(domElement, AttrName);
209 }
210 else
211 {
212 changeActiveDraftBlock(GetParametrString(domElement, AttrName), Document::LiteParse);
213 }
214 parseDraftBlockElement(domElement, parse);
215 break;
216 case 1: // TagVariables
217 qCDebug(vXML, "Tag variables.");
218 parseVariablesElement(domElement);
219 break;
220 case 2: // TagDescription
221 qCDebug(vXML, "Tag description.");
222 break;
223 case 3: // TagNotes
224 qCDebug(vXML, "Tag notes.");
225 break;
226 case 4: // TagMeasurements
227 qCDebug(vXML, "Tag measurements.");
228 break;
229 case 5: // TagVersion
230 qCDebug(vXML, "Tag version.");
231 break;
232 case 6: // TagGradation
233 qCDebug(vXML, "Tag gradation.");
234 break;
235 case 7: // TagImage
236 qCDebug(vXML, "Tag image.");
237 break;
238 case 8: // TagUnit
239 qCDebug(vXML, "Tag unit.");
240 break;
241 case 9: // TagPatternName
242 qCDebug(vXML, "Pattern name.");
243 break;
244 case 10: // TagPatternNumber
245 qCDebug(vXML, "Pattern number.");
246 break;
247 case 11: // TagCompanyName
248 qCDebug(vXML, "Company name.");
249 break;
250 case 12: // TagCustomerName
251 qCDebug(vXML, "Customer name.");
252 break;
253 case 13: // TagPatternLabel
254 qCDebug(vXML, "Pattern label.");
255 break;
256 default:
257 qCDebug(vXML, "Wrong tag name %s", qUtf8Printable(domElement.tagName()));
258 break;
259 }
260 }
261 }
262 domNode = domNode.nextSibling();
263 }
264 emit patternParsed();
265}

267//---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
268/**
269 * @brief setCurrentData set current data set.
270 *
271 * Each time after parsing need set correct data set for current draft block. After parsing it is always last.
272 * Current data set for draft block it is data set for last object in draft block (point, arc, spline, spline path so
273 * on).
274 */
275void VPattern::setCurrentData()
276{
277 if (*mode == Draw::Calculation)
278 {
279 if (draftBlockCount() > 1)//don't need to update data if we have only one draft block
280 {
281 qCDebug(vXML, "Setting current data");
282 qCDebug(vXML, "Current Draft block name %s", qUtf8Printable(activeDraftBlock));
283 qCDebug(vXML, "Draftf block count %d", draftBlockCount());
284
285 quint32 id = 0;
286 if (history.size() == 0)
287 {
288 qCDebug(vXML, "History is empty!");
289 return;
290 }
291 for (qint32 i = 0; i < history.size(); ++i)
292 {
293 const VToolRecord tool = history.at(i);
294 if (tool.getDraftBlockName() == activeDraftBlock)
295 {
296 id = tool.getId();
297 }
298 }
299 qCDebug(vXML, "Resoring data from tool with id %u", id);
300 if (id == NULL_ID)
301 {
302 qCDebug(vXML, "Could not find record for this current draft block %s",
303 qUtf8Printable(activeDraftBlock));
304
305 const VToolRecord tool = history.at(history.size()-1);
306 id = tool.getId();
307 qCDebug(vXML, "Taking record with id %u from Draft block %s", id, qUtf8Printable(tool.getDraftBlockName()));
308 if (id == NULL_ID)
309 {
310 qCDebug(vXML, "Bad id for last record in history.");
311 return;
312 }
313 }
314 if (tools.size() > 0)
315 {
316 try
317 {
318 ToolExists(id);
319 }
320 catch (VExceptionBadId &error)
321 {
322 Q_UNUSED(error)
323 qCDebug(vXML, "List of tools doesn't contain id= %u", id);
324 return;
325 }
326
327 const VDataTool *vTool = tools.value(id);
328 *data = vTool->getData();
329 //Delete special variables if exist
330 data->RemoveVariable(currentLength);
331 data->RemoveVariable(currentSeamAllowance);
332 qCDebug(vXML, "Data successfully updated.");
333 }
334 else
335 {
336 qCDebug(vXML, "List of tools is empty!");
337 }
338 }
339 }
340}

349{

359/**
360 * @brief getActiveBasePoint return id base point current draft block.
361 * @return id base point.
362 */
363// cppcheck-suppress unusedFunction
364quint32 VPattern::getActiveBasePoint()
365{
366 QDomElement calcElement;
367 if (getActiveNodeElement(TagCalculation, calcElement))
368 {
369 const QDomNode domNode = calcElement.firstChild();
370 if (domNode.isNull() == false && domNode.isElement())
371 {
372 const QDomElement domElement = domNode.toElement();
373 if (domElement.isNull() == false)
374 {
375 if (domElement.tagName() == TagPoint && domElement.attribute(AttrType, "") == VToolBasePoint::ToolType)
376 {
377 return getParameterId(domElement);
378 }
379 }
380 }
381 }
382 return 0;
383}

385//---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
386QVector<quint32> VPattern::getActivePatternPieces() const
387{
388 QVector<quint32> pieces;
389 QDomElement drawElement;
390 if (getActiveDraftElement(drawElement))
391 {
392 const QDomElement elements = drawElement.firstChildElement(TagPieces);
393 if (!elements.isNull())
394 {
395 QDomElement piece = elements.firstChildElement(TagPiece);
396 while(!piece.isNull())
397 {
398 bool united = getParameterBool(piece, PatternPieceTool::AttrUnited, falseStr);
399 if (!united)
400 {
401 pieces.append(getParameterId(piece));
402 }
403 piece = piece.nextSiblingElement(TagPiece);
404 }
405 }
406 }
407 return pieces;
408}

410//---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
411bool VPattern::SaveDocument(const QString &fileName, QString &error)
412{
413 try
414 {
415 TestUniqueId();
416 }
417 catch (const VExceptionWrongId &error)
418 {
419 qCCritical(vXML, "%s\n\n%s\n\n%s", qUtf8Printable(tr("Error not unique id.")),
420 qUtf8Printable(error.ErrorMessage()), qUtf8Printable(error.DetailedInformation()));
421 return false;
422 }
423
424 // Update comment with Seamly2D version
425 QDomNode commentNode = documentElement().firstChild();
426 if (commentNode.isComment())
427 {
428 QDomComment comment = commentNode.toComment();
429 comment.setData(FileComment());
430 }
431
432 const bool saved = VAbstractPattern::SaveDocument(fileName, error);
433 if (saved && QFileInfo(fileName).suffix() != QLatin1String("autosave"))
434 {
435 modified = false;
436 }
437
438 return saved;
439}

441//---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
442void VPattern::LiteParseVariables()
443{
444 try
445 {
446 emit setGuiEnabled(true);
447
448 VContainer::clearUniqueVariableNames();
449 data->ClearVariables(VarType::Variable);
450
451 const QDomNodeList tags = elementsByTagName(TagVariables);
452 if (not tags.isEmpty())
453 {
454 const QDomNode domElement = tags.at(0);
455 if (not domElement.isNull())
456 {
457 parseVariablesElement(domElement);
458 }
459 }
460 }
461 catch (const VExceptionUndo &error)
462 {
463 Q_UNUSED(error)
464 /* If user want undo last operation before undo we need finish broken redo operation. For those we post event
465 * myself. Later in method customEvent call undo.*/
466 QApplication::postEvent(this, new UndoEvent());
467 return;
468 }
469 catch (const VExceptionObjectError &error)
470 {
471 qCCritical(vXML, "%s\n\n%s\n\n%s", qUtf8Printable(tr("Error parsing file.")), //-V807
472 qUtf8Printable(error.ErrorMessage()), qUtf8Printable(error.DetailedInformation()));
473 emit setGuiEnabled(false);
474 return;
475 }
476 catch (const VExceptionConversionError &error)
477 {
478 qCCritical(vXML, "%s\n\n%s\n\n%s", qUtf8Printable(tr("Error can't convert value.")),
479 qUtf8Printable(error.ErrorMessage()), qUtf8Printable(error.DetailedInformation()));
480 emit setGuiEnabled(false);
481 return;
482 }
483 catch (const VExceptionEmptyParameter &error)
484 {
485 qCCritical(vXML, "%s\n\n%s\n\n%s", qUtf8Printable(tr("Error empty parameter.")),
486 qUtf8Printable(error.ErrorMessage()), qUtf8Printable(error.DetailedInformation()));
487 emit setGuiEnabled(false);
488 return;
489 }
490 catch (const VExceptionWrongId &error)
491 {
492 qCCritical(vXML, "%s\n\n%s\n\n%s", qUtf8Printable(tr("Error wrong id.")),
493 qUtf8Printable(error.ErrorMessage()), qUtf8Printable(error.DetailedInformation()));
494 emit setGuiEnabled(false);
495 return;
496 }
497 catch (VException &error)
498 {
499 qCCritical(vXML, "%s\n\n%s\n\n%s", qUtf8Printable(tr("Error parsing file.")),
500 qUtf8Printable(error.ErrorMessage()), qUtf8Printable(error.DetailedInformation()));
501 emit setGuiEnabled(false);
502 return;
503 }
504 catch (const std::bad_alloc &)
505 {
506 qCCritical(vXML, "%s", qUtf8Printable(tr("Error parsing file (std::bad_alloc).")));
507 emit setGuiEnabled(false);
508 return;
509 }
510}

513/**
514 * @brief LiteParseTree lite parse file.
515 */
516void VPattern::LiteParseTree(const Document &parse)
517{
518 // Save current draft block name
519 QString draftBlockName = activeDraftBlock;
520
521 try
522 {
523 emit setGuiEnabled(true);
524 switch (parse)
525 {
526 case Document::LiteBlockParse:
527 parseCurrentDraftBlock();
528 break;
529 case Document::LiteParse:
530 Parse(parse);
531 break;
532 case Document::FullParse:
533 qCWarning(vXML, "Lite parsing doesn't support full parsing");
534 break;
535 default:
536 break;
537 }
538 }
539 catch (const VExceptionUndo &error)
540 {
541 Q_UNUSED(error)
542 /* If user want undo last operation before undo we need finish broken redo operation. For those we post event
543 * myself. Later in method customEvent call undo.*/
544 QApplication::postEvent(this, new UndoEvent());
545 return;
546 }
547 catch (const VExceptionObjectError &error)
548 {
549 qCCritical(vXML, "%s\n\n%s\n\n%s", qUtf8Printable(tr("Error parsing file.")), //-V807
550 qUtf8Printable(error.ErrorMessage()), qUtf8Printable(error.DetailedInformation()));
551 emit setGuiEnabled(false);
552 if (not Application2D::isGUIMode())
553 {
554 qApp->exit(V_EX_NOINPUT);
555 }
556 return;
557 }
558 catch (const VExceptionConversionError &error)
559 {
560 qCCritical(vXML, "%s\n\n%s\n\n%s", qUtf8Printable(tr("Error can't convert value.")),
561 qUtf8Printable(error.ErrorMessage()), qUtf8Printable(error.DetailedInformation()));
562 emit setGuiEnabled(false);
563 if (not Application2D::isGUIMode())
564 {
565 qApp->exit(V_EX_NOINPUT);
566 }
567 return;
568 }
569 catch (const VExceptionEmptyParameter &error)
570 {
571 qCCritical(vXML, "%s\n\n%s\n\n%s", qUtf8Printable(tr("Error empty parameter.")),
572 qUtf8Printable(error.ErrorMessage()), qUtf8Printable(error.DetailedInformation()));
573 emit setGuiEnabled(false);
574 if (not Application2D::isGUIMode())
575 {
576 qApp->exit(V_EX_NOINPUT);
577 }
578 return;
579 }
580 catch (const VExceptionWrongId &error)
581 {
582 qCCritical(vXML, "%s\n\n%s\n\n%s", qUtf8Printable(tr("Error wrong id.")),
583 qUtf8Printable(error.ErrorMessage()), qUtf8Printable(error.DetailedInformation()));
584 emit setGuiEnabled(false);
585 if (not Application2D::isGUIMode())
586 {
587 qApp->exit(V_EX_NOINPUT);
588 }
589 return;
590 }
591 catch (VException &error)
592 {
593 qCCritical(vXML, "%s\n\n%s\n\n%s", qUtf8Printable(tr("Error parsing file.")),
594 qUtf8Printable(error.ErrorMessage()), qUtf8Printable(error.DetailedInformation()));
595 emit setGuiEnabled(false);
596 if (not Application2D::isGUIMode())
597 {
598 qApp->exit(V_EX_NOINPUT);
599 }
600 return;
601 }
602 catch (const std::bad_alloc &)
603 {
604 qCCritical(vXML, "%s", qUtf8Printable(tr("Error parsing file (std::bad_alloc).")));
605 emit setGuiEnabled(false);
606 if (not Application2D::isGUIMode())
607 {
608 qApp->exit(V_EX_NOINPUT);
609 }
610 return;
611 }
612
613 // Restore name current draft block
614 activeDraftBlock = draftBlockName;
615 qCDebug(vXML, "Current draft block %s", qUtf8Printable(activeDraftBlock));
616 setCurrentData();
617 emit FullUpdateFromFile();
618 // Recalculate scene rect
619 VMainGraphicsView::NewSceneRect(draftScene, qApp->getSceneView());
620 VMainGraphicsView::NewSceneRect(pieceScene, qApp->getSceneView());
621 qCDebug(vXML, "Scene size updated.");
622}

638//---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
639VNodeDetail VPattern::parsePieceNode(const QDomElement &domElement) const
640{
641 const quint32 id = GetParametrUInt(domElement, AttrIdObject, NULL_ID_STR);
642 const qreal mx = GetParametrDouble(domElement, AttrMx, "0.0");
643 const qreal my = GetParametrDouble(domElement, AttrMy, "0.0");
644 const bool reverse = GetParametrUInt(domElement, VAbstractPattern::AttrNodeReverse, "0");
645 const NodeDetail nodeType = NodeDetail::Contour;
646
647 const QString t = GetParametrString(domElement, AttrType, "NodePoint");
648 Tool tool;
649
650 QStringList types = QStringList() << VAbstractPattern::NodePoint
651 << VAbstractPattern::NodeArc
652 << VAbstractPattern::NodeSpline
653 << VAbstractPattern::NodeSplinePath
654 << VAbstractPattern::NodeElArc;
655 switch (types.indexOf(t))
656 {
657 case 0: // NodePoint
658 tool = Tool::NodePoint;
659 break;
660 case 1: // NodeArc
661 tool = Tool::NodeArc;
662 break;
663 case 2: // NodeSpline
664 tool = Tool::NodeSpline;
665 break;
666 case 3: // NodeSplinePath
667 tool = Tool::NodeSplinePath;
668 break;
669 case 4: // NodeElArc
670 tool = Tool::NodeElArc;
671 break;
672 default:
673 VException e(tr("Wrong tag name '%1'.").arg(t));
674 throw e;
675 }
676 return VNodeDetail(id, tool, nodeType, mx, my, reverse);
677}

679//---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
680/**
681 * @brief parseDraftBlockElement parse draw tag.
682 * @param node node.
683 * @param parse parser file mode.
684 */
685void VPattern::parseDraftBlockElement(const QDomNode &node, const Document &parse)
686{
687 QStringList tags = QStringList() << TagCalculation << TagModeling << TagPieces << TagGroups << TagDraftImages;
688 QDomNode domNode = node.firstChild();
689 while (domNode.isNull() == false)
690 {
691 if (domNode.isElement())
692 {
693 const QDomElement domElement = domNode.toElement();
694 if (domElement.isNull() == false)
695 {
696 switch (tags.indexOf(domElement.tagName()))
697 {
698 case 0: // TagCalculation
699 qCDebug(vXML, "Tag calculation.");
700 data->ClearCalculationGObjects();
701 ParseDrawMode(domElement, parse, Draw::Calculation);
702 break;
703 case 1: // TagModeling
704 qCDebug(vXML, "Tag modeling.");
705 ParseDrawMode(domElement, parse, Draw::Modeling);
706 break;
707 case 2: // TagPieces
708 qCDebug(vXML, "Tag pieces.");
709 parsePatternPieces(domElement, parse);
710 break;
711 case 3: // TagGroups
712 qCDebug(vXML, "Tag groups.");
713 parseGroups(domElement);
714 break;
715 case 4: // TagDraftImages
716 qCDebug(vXML, "Tag draft images.");
717 parseDraftImages(domElement, parse);
718 break;
719 default:
720 VException e(tr("Wrong tag name '%1'.").arg(domElement.tagName()));
721 throw e;
722 }
723 }
724 }
725 domNode = domNode.nextSibling();
726 }
727}

729//---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
730/**
731 * @brief ParseDrawMode parse draw tag with draw mode.
732 * @param node node.
733 * @param parse parser file mode.
734 * @param mode draw mode.
735 */
736void VPattern::ParseDrawMode(const QDomNode &node, const Document &parse, const Draw &mode)
737{
738 SCASSERT(draftScene != nullptr)
739 SCASSERT(pieceScene != nullptr)
740 VMainGraphicsScene *scene = nullptr;
741 if (mode == Draw::Calculation)
742 {
743 scene = draftScene;
744 }
745 else
746 {
747 scene = pieceScene;
748 }
749 const QStringList tags = QStringList() << TagPoint
750 << TagLine
751 << TagSpline
752 << TagArc
753 << TagTools
754 << TagOperation
755 << TagElArc
756 << TagPath;
757 const QDomNodeList nodeList = node.childNodes();
758 const qint32 num = nodeList.size();
759 for (qint32 i = 0; i < num; ++i)
760 {
761 QDomElement domElement = nodeList.at(i).toElement();
762 if (domElement.isNull() == false)
763 {
764 switch (tags.indexOf(domElement.tagName()))
765 {
766 case 0: // TagPoint
767 qCDebug(vXML, "Tag point.");
768 ParsePointElement(scene, domElement, parse, domElement.attribute(AttrType, ""));
769 break;
770 case 1: // TagLine
771 qCDebug(vXML, "Tag line.");
772 ParseLineElement(scene, domElement, parse);
773 break;
774 case 2: // TagSpline
775 qCDebug(vXML, "Tag spline.");
776 ParseSplineElement(scene, domElement, parse, domElement.attribute(AttrType, ""));
777 break;
778 case 3: // TagArc
779 qCDebug(vXML, "Tag arc.");
780 ParseArcElement(scene, domElement, parse, domElement.attribute(AttrType, ""));
781 break;
782 case 4: // TagTools
783 qCDebug(vXML, "Tag tools.");
784 ParseToolsElement(scene, domElement, parse, domElement.attribute(AttrType, ""));
785 break;
786 case 5: // TagOperation
787 qCDebug(vXML, "Tag operation.");
788 ParseOperationElement(scene, domElement, parse, domElement.attribute(AttrType, ""));
789 break;
790 case 6: // TagElArc
791 qCDebug(vXML, "Tag elliptical arc.");
792 ParseEllipticalArcElement(scene, domElement, parse, domElement.attribute(AttrType, ""));
793 break;
794 case 7: // TagPath
795 qCDebug(vXML, "Tag path.");
796 ParsePathElement(scene, domElement, parse);
797 break;
798 default:
799 VException e(tr("Wrong tag name '%1'.").arg(domElement.tagName()));
800 throw e;
801 }
802 }
803 }
804}

837//---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
838/**
839 * @brief parsePieceElement parse piece tag.
840 * @param domElement tag in xml tree.
841 * @param parse parser file mode.
842 */
843void VPattern::parsePieceElement(QDomElement &domElement, const Document &parse)
844{
845 Q_ASSERT_X(not domElement.isNull(), Q_FUNC_INFO, "domElement is null");
846 try
847 {
848 VPiece piece;
849 const quint32 id = getParameterId(domElement);
850 piece.SetName(GetParametrString(domElement, AttrName, tr("Piece")));
851 piece.setColor(GetParametrString(domElement, PatternPieceTool::AttrPieceColor, tr("white")));
852 piece.setFill(GetParametrString(domElement, PatternPieceTool::AttrPieceFill, tr("nobrush")));
853 piece.setIsLocked(getParameterBool(domElement, AttrPieceLocked, falseStr));
854
855 piece.SetMx(qApp->toPixel(GetParametrDouble(domElement, AttrMx, "0.0")));
856 piece.SetMy(qApp->toPixel(GetParametrDouble(domElement, AttrMy, "0.0")));
857 piece.SetSeamAllowance(getParameterBool(domElement, PatternPieceTool::AttrSeamAllowance, falseStr));
858 piece.setHideSeamLine(getParameterBool(domElement, PatternPieceTool::AttrHideSeamLine,
859 QString().setNum(qApp->Seamly2DSettings()->isHideSeamLine())));
860 piece.SetSeamAllowanceBuiltIn(getParameterBool(domElement, PatternPieceTool::AttrSeamAllowanceBuiltIn,
861 falseStr));
862 piece.SetForbidFlipping(getParameterBool(domElement, PatternPieceTool::AttrForbidFlipping,
863 QString().setNum(qApp->Seamly2DSettings()->getForbidPieceFlipping())));
864 piece.SetInLayout(getParameterBool(domElement, AttrInLayout, trueStr));
865 piece.SetUnited(getParameterBool(domElement, PatternPieceTool::AttrUnited, falseStr));
866
867 const QString width = GetParametrString(domElement, AttrWidth, "0.0");
868 QString w = width;//need for saving fixed formula;
869 const uint version = GetParametrUInt(domElement, PatternPieceTool::AttrVersion, "1");
870
871 const QStringList tags = QStringList() << TagNodes
872 << TagData
873 << TagPatternInfo
874 << TagGrainline
875 << PatternPieceTool::TagCSA
876 << PatternPieceTool::TagIPaths
877 << PatternPieceTool::TagAnchors;
878
879 const QDomNodeList nodeList = domElement.childNodes();
880 for (qint32 i = 0; i < nodeList.size(); ++i)
881 {
882 const QDomElement element = nodeList.at(i).toElement();
883 if (not element.isNull())
884 {
885 switch (tags.indexOf(element.tagName()))
886 {
887 case 0:// TagNodes
888 if (version == 1)
889 {
890 // TODO. Delete if minimal supported version is 0.4.0
891 Q_STATIC_ASSERT_X(VPatternConverter::PatternMinVer < CONVERTER_VERSION_CHECK(0, 4, 0),
892 "Time to refactor the code.");
893 const bool closed = GetParametrUInt(domElement, AttrClosed, "1");
894 const qreal width = GetParametrDouble(domElement, AttrWidth, "0.0");
895 parsePieceNodes(element, piece, width, closed);
896 }
897 else
898 {
899 piece.SetPath(ParsePieceNodes(element));
900 }
901 break;
902 case 1:// TagData
903 ParsePieceDataTag(element, piece);
904 break;
905 case 2:// TagPatternInfo
906 ParsePiecePatternInfo(element, piece);
907 break;
908 case 3:// TagGrainline
909 ParsePieceGrainline(element, piece);
910 break;
911 case 4:// PatternPieceTool::TagCSA
912 piece.SetCustomSARecords(ParsePieceCSARecords(element));
913 break;
914 case 5:// PatternPieceTool::TagIPaths
915 piece.SetInternalPaths(ParsePieceInternalPaths(element));
916 break;
917 case 6:// PatternPieceTool::TagAnchors
918 piece.setAnchors(ParsePieceAnchors(element));
919 break;
920 default:
921 break;
922 }
923 }
924 }
925 PatternPieceTool::Create(id, piece, w, pieceScene, this, data, parse, Source::FromFile);
926 //Rewrite attribute formula. Need for situation when we have wrong formula.
927 if (w != width)
928 {
929 SetAttribute(domElement, AttrWidth, w);
930 modified = true;
931 haveLiteChange();
932 }
933 }
934 catch (const VExceptionBadId &error)
935 {
936 VExceptionObjectError excep(tr("Error creating or updating piece"), domElement);
937 excep.AddMoreInformation(error.ErrorMessage());
938 throw excep;
939 }
940}

943//---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
944/**
945 * @brief parseImageElement parse image tag.
946 * @param domElement tag in xml tree.
947 */
948void VPattern::parseImageElement(QDomElement &domElement, const Document &parse)
949{
950 Q_ASSERT_X(not domElement.isNull(), Q_FUNC_INFO, "domElement is null");
951
952 DraftImage image;
953
954 image.id = getParameterId(domElement);
955 image.name = GetParametrString(domElement, AttrName, tr("Image_name"));
956 image.filename = GetParametrString(domElement, AttrSource);
957 image.width = GetParametrDouble(domElement, AttrWidth, "0.0");
958 image.height = GetParametrDouble(domElement, AttrHeight, "0.0");
959 image.xPos = GetParametrDouble(domElement, AttrXPos, "0.0");
960 image.yPos = GetParametrDouble(domElement, AttrYPos, "0.0");
961 image.rotation = GetParametrDouble(domElement, AttrRotation, "0.0");
962 image.aspectLocked = getParameterBool(domElement, AttrAspectRatio, falseStr);
963 image.locked = getParameterBool(domElement, AttrLocked, falseStr);
964 image.units = StrToUnits(GetParametrString(domElement, AttrUnits, "px"));
965 image.opacity = GetParametrDouble(domElement, AttrOpacity, "1.0");
966 image.order = qint32(GetParametrDouble(domElement, AttrOrder, "0"));
967 image.xOrigin = GetParametrDouble(domElement, AttrXOffset, "0.0");
968 image.yOrigin = GetParametrDouble(domElement, AttrYOffset, "0.0");
969 image.basepoint = GetParametrUInt(domElement, AttrBasepoint, 0);
970 image.visible = getParameterBool(domElement, AttrVisible, trueStr);
971
972 VContainer::UpdateId(image.id);
973
974 if(parse == Document::FullParse)
975 {
976 ImageTool *image_tool = new ImageTool(this, this, draftScene, image);
977 if(image_tool->creationWasSuccessful)
978 {
979 connect(image_tool, &ImageTool::setStatusMessage, this, [this](QString message) {emit setStatusMessage(message);});
980 }
981 else
982 {
983 image_tool->deleteLater();
984 ParentNodeById(image.id).removeChild(domElement); //this way the broken image is not light-parsed in the future
985 }
986 }
987 else
988 {
989 getBackgroundImage(image.id)->updateImageAndHandles(image);
990 }
991}

994//---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
995void VPattern::parsePieceNodes(const QDomElement &domElement, VPiece &piece, qreal width, bool closed) const
996{
997 QVector<VNodeDetail> oldNodes;
998 const QDomNodeList nodeList = domElement.childNodes();
999 for (qint32 i = 0; i < nodeList.size(); ++i)
1000 {
1001 const QDomElement element = nodeList.at(i).toElement();
1002 if (not element.isNull()
1003 && element.tagName() == VAbstractPattern::TagNode) // Old piece version need this check!
1004 {
1005 oldNodes.append(parsePieceNode(element));
1006 }
1007 }
1008
1009 piece.GetPath().SetNodes(VNodeDetail::Convert(data, oldNodes, width, closed));
1010}

1066/**
1067 * @brief parsePatternPieces parse pieces tag.
1068 * @param domElement tag in xml tree.
1069 * @param parse parser file mode.
1070 */
1071void VPattern::parsePatternPieces(const QDomElement &domElement, const Document &parse)
1072{
1073 Q_ASSERT_X(not domElement.isNull(), Q_FUNC_INFO, "domElement is null");
1074 QDomNode domNode = domElement.firstChild();
1075 while (domNode.isNull() == false)
1076 {
1077 if (domNode.isElement())
1078 {
1079 QDomElement domElement = domNode.toElement();
1080 if (domElement.isNull() == false)
1081 {
1082 if (domElement.tagName() == TagPiece)
1083 {
1084 parsePieceElement(domElement, parse);
1085 }
1086 }
1087 }
1088 domNode = domNode.nextSibling();
1089 }
1090}

1130{

1132 Q_ASSERT_X(not domElement.isNull(), Q_FUNC_INFO, "domElement is null");
1133 Q_ASSERT_X(not type.isEmpty(), Q_FUNC_INFO, "type of point is empty");

1136 << VToolEndLine::ToolType /*1*/
1137 << VToolAlongLine::ToolType /*2*/
1138 << VToolShoulderPoint::ToolType /*3*/

1141 << VToolLineIntersect::ToolType /*6*/
1142 << VToolPointOfContact::ToolType /*7*/
1143 << VNodePoint::ToolType /*8*/
1144 << VToolHeight::ToolType /*9*/

1147 << VToolCutSpline::ToolType /*12*/
1148 << VToolCutSplinePath::ToolType /*13*/

1151 << VToolCurveIntersectAxis::ToolType /*16*/

1156 << VToolTrueDarts::ToolType /*21*/
1157 << VToolPointOfIntersectionCurves::ToolType /*22*/
1158 << AnchorPointTool::ToolType; /*23*/
1159 switch (points.indexOf(type))
1160 {

1163 break;
1164 case 1: //VToolEndLine::ToolType

1169 break;
1170 case 3: //VToolShoulderPoint::ToolType
1171 ParseToolShoulderPoint(scene, domElement, parse);
1172 break;
1173 case 4: //VToolNormal::ToolType
1174 ParseToolNormal(scene, domElement, parse);
1175 break;

1177 ParseToolBisector(scene, domElement, parse);
1178 break;
1179 case 6: //VToolLineIntersect::ToolType
1180 ParseToolLineIntersect(scene, domElement, parse);
1181 break;
1182 case 7: //VToolPointOfContact::ToolType
1183 ParseToolPointOfContact(scene, domElement, parse);
1184 break;
1185 case 8: //VNodePoint::ToolType
1186 ParseNodePoint(domElement, parse);
1187 break;
1188 case 9: //VToolHeight::ToolType
1189 ParseToolHeight(scene, domElement, parse);
1190 break;
1191 case 10: //VToolTriangle::ToolType
1192 ParseToolTriangle(scene, domElement, parse);
1193 break;
1194 case 11: //PointIntersectXYTool::ToolType
1195 parseIntersectXYTool(scene, domElement, parse);
1196 break;
1197 case 12: //VToolCutSpline::ToolType
1198 ParseToolCutSpline(scene, domElement, parse);
1199 break;
1200 case 13: //VToolCutSplinePath::ToolType
1201 ParseToolCutSplinePath(scene, domElement, parse);
1202 break;
1203 case 14: //VToolCutArc::ToolType
1204 ParseToolCutArc(scene, domElement, parse);

1213 ParseToolPointOfIntersectionArcs(scene, domElement, parse);
1214 break;
1215 case 18: //IntersectCirclesTool::ToolType
1216 ParseToolPointOfIntersectionCircles(scene, domElement, parse);
1217 break;
1218 case 19: //IntersectCircleTangentTool::ToolType
1219 ParseToolPointFromCircleAndTangent(scene, domElement, parse);

1227 case 22: //VToolPointOfIntersectionCurves::ToolType

1230 case 23: //AnchorPointTool::ToolType
1231 ParseAnchorPoint(domElement, parse);

1236 }

1330 break;
1331 }
1332 case 6: // sr
1333 {
1334 const QString al = QStringLiteral(",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,");
1335 alphabet = al.split(",");
1336 break;
1337 }
1338 case 1: // en
1339 default: // en
1340 {
1341 alphabet = def.split(",");
1342 break;
1343 }
1344 }
1345
1346 return alphabet;
1347}
1348
1349//---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1350QString VPattern::GetLabelBase(quint32 index) const
1351{
1352 QStringList alphabet = GetCurrentAlphabet();
1353 QString base;
1354 const int count = qFloor(index/static_cast<quint32>(alphabet.size()));
1355 const int number = static_cast<int>(index) - alphabet.size() * count;
1356 int i = 0;
1357 do
1358 {
1359 base.append(alphabet.at(number));
1360 ++i;
1361 } while (i < count);
1362 return base;
1363}

2494void VPattern::ParseOldToolSplinePath(VMainGraphicsScene *scene, const QDomElement &domElement, const Document &parse)

2509
2510 const QDomNodeList nodeList = domElement.childNodes();
2511 const qint32 num = nodeList.size();
2512 for (qint32 i = 0; i < num; ++i)

2526 line.setAngle(angle+180);

2535 }
2536 }

2539 if (duplicate > 0)
2540 {
2541 path->SetDuplicate(duplicate);
2542 }
2543 path->setLineColor(color);
2544
2545 VToolSplinePath::Create(id, path, scene, this, data, parse, Source::FromFile);
2546 }
2547 catch (const VExceptionBadId &error)

2555//---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2556void VPattern::ParseToolSplinePath(VMainGraphicsScene *scene, const QDomElement &domElement, const Document &parse)
2557{
2558 SCASSERT(scene != nullptr)
2559 Q_ASSERT_X(not domElement.isNull(), Q_FUNC_INFO, "domElement is null");
2560
2561 try
2562 {
2563 quint32 id = 0;
2564
2565 ToolsCommonAttributes(domElement, id);
2566 const QString color = GetParametrString(domElement, AttrColor, ColorBlack);
2567 const QString penStyle = GetParametrString(domElement, AttrPenStyle, LineTypeSolidLine);
2568 const QString lineWeight = GetParametrString(domElement, AttrLineWeight, "0.35");
2569 const quint32 duplicate = GetParametrUInt(domElement, AttrDuplicate, "0");
2570
2571 QVector<quint32> points;
2572 QVector<QString> angle1, a1;
2573 QVector<QString> angle2, a2;
2574 QVector<QString> length1, l1;
2575 QVector<QString> length2, l2;
2576
2577 const QDomNodeList nodeList = domElement.childNodes();
2578 const qint32 num = nodeList.size();
2579 for (qint32 i = 0; i < num; ++i)
2580 {
2581 const QDomElement element = nodeList.at(i).toElement();
2582 if (not element.isNull() && element.tagName() == AttrPathPoint)
2583 {
2584 angle1.append(GetParametrString(element, AttrAngle1, "0"));
2585 angle2.append(GetParametrString(element, AttrAngle2, "0"));
2586 length1.append(GetParametrString(element, AttrLength1, "0"));
2587 length2.append(GetParametrString(element, AttrLength2, "0"));
2588 const quint32 pSpline = GetParametrUInt(element, AttrPSpline, NULL_ID_STR);
2589 points.append(pSpline);
2590
2591 if (parse == Document::FullParse)
2592 {
2593 IncrementReferens(data->GeometricObject<VPointF>(pSpline)->getIdTool());
2594 }
2595 }
2596 }
2597
2598 //need for saving fixed formula;
2599 a1 = angle1;
2600 a2 = angle2;
2601 l1 = length1;
2602 l2 = length2;
2603
2604 VToolSplinePath *spl = VToolSplinePath::Create(id, points, a1, a2, l1, l2, color, penStyle, lineWeight,
2605 duplicate, scene, this, data, parse, Source::FromFile);
2606
2607 if (spl != nullptr)
2608 {
2609 VAbstractMainWindow *window = qobject_cast<VAbstractMainWindow *>(qApp->getMainWindow());
2610 SCASSERT(window != nullptr)
2611 connect(spl, &VToolSplinePath::ToolTip, window, &VAbstractMainWindow::ShowToolTip);
2612 }
2613
2614 //Rewrite attribute formula. Need for situation when we have wrong formula.
2615 int count = 0;
2616 for (qint32 i = 0; i < num; ++i)
2617 {
2618 QDomElement element = nodeList.at(i).toElement();
2619 if (not element.isNull() && element.tagName() == AttrPathPoint)
2620 {
2621 if (a1.at(count) != angle1.at(count) || a2.at(count) != angle2.at(count) ||
2622 l1.at(count) != length1.at(count) || l2.at(count) != length2.at(count))
2623 {
2624 SetAttribute(element, AttrAngle1, a1.at(count));
2625 SetAttribute(element, AttrAngle2, a2.at(count));
2626 SetAttribute(element, AttrLength1, l1.at(count));
2627 SetAttribute(element, AttrLength2, l2.at(count));
2628 modified = true;
2629 haveLiteChange();
2630 }
2631 ++count;
2632 }
2633 }
2634 }
2635 catch (const VExceptionBadId &error)
2636 {
2637 VExceptionObjectError excep(tr("Error creating or updating curve path"), domElement);
2638 excep.AddMoreInformation(error.ErrorMessage());
2639 throw excep;
2640 }
2641 catch (qmu::QmuParserError &error)
2642 {
2643 VExceptionObjectError excep(tr("Error creating or updating interactive spline path"), domElement);
2644 excep.AddMoreInformation(QString("Message: " + error.GetMsg() + "\n"+ "Expression: " + error.GetExpr()));
2645 throw excep;
2646 }

3236void VPattern::GarbageCollector()
3237{
3238 QDomNodeList modelingList = elementsByTagName(TagModeling);
3239 for (int i=0; i < modelingList.size(); ++i)
3240 {
3241 QDomElement modElement = modelingList.at(i).toElement();
3242 if (not modElement.isNull())
3243 {
3244 QDomElement modNode = modElement.firstChild().toElement();
3245 while (not modNode.isNull())
3246 {
3247 // First get next sibling because later will not have chance to get it
3248 QDomElement nextSibling = modNode.nextSibling().toElement();
3249 if (modNode.hasAttribute(VAbstractNode::AttrInUse))
3250 {
3251 const NodeUsage inUse = GetParametrUsage(modNode, VAbstractNode::AttrInUse);
3252 if (inUse == NodeUsage::InUse)
3253 { // It is dangerous to leave object with attribute 'inUse'
3254 // Each parse should confirm this status.
3255 SetParametrUsage(modNode, VAbstractNode::AttrInUse, NodeUsage::NotInUse);
3256 }
3257 else
3258 { // Parent was deleted. We do not need this object anymore
3259 modElement.removeChild(modNode);
3260 }
3261 }
3262 else
3263 { // Each parse should confirm his status.
3264 SetParametrUsage(modNode, VAbstractNode::AttrInUse, NodeUsage::NotInUse);
3265 }
3266
3267 modNode = nextSibling;
3268 }
3269 }

3669//---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3670void VPattern::replaceNameInFormula(QVector<VFormulaField> &expressions, const QString &name, const QString &newName)
3671{
3672 const int bias = name.length() - newName.length();
3673
3674 for(int i = 0; i < expressions.size(); ++i)
3675 {
3676 if (expressions.at(i).expression.indexOf(name) != -1)
3677 {
3678 QMap<int, QString> tokens;
3679
3680 // Eval formula
3681 try
3682 {
3683 QScopedPointer<qmu::QmuTokenParser> cal(new qmu::QmuTokenParser(expressions.at(i).expression, false,
3684 false));
3685 tokens = cal->GetTokens();// Tokens (variables, measurements)
3686
3687 }
3688 catch (const qmu::QmuParserError &)
3689 {
3690 continue;// Because we not sure if used. A formula is broken.
3691 }
3692
3693 QList<QString> tValues = tokens.values();
3694 if (not tValues.contains(name))
3695 {
3696 continue;
3697 }
3698
3699 QList<int> tKeys = tokens.keys();// Take all tokens positions
3700 QString newFormula = expressions.at(i).expression;
3701
3702 for (int i = 0; i < tKeys.size(); ++i)
3703 {
3704 if (tValues.at(i) != name)
3705 {
3706 continue;
3707 }
3708
3709 newFormula.replace(tKeys.at(i), name.length(), newName);
3710
3711 if (bias != 0)
3712 {// Translated token has different length than original. Position next tokens need to be corrected.
3713 VTranslateVars::BiasTokens(tKeys.at(i), bias, tokens);
3714 tKeys = tokens.keys();
3715 tValues = tokens.values();
3716 }
3717 }
3718
3719 expressions[i].expression = newFormula;
3720 expressions[i].element.setAttribute(expressions.at(i).attribute, newFormula);
3721 emit patternChanged(false);
3722 }
3723 }
3724}

3727/**
3728 * @brief GenerateLabel create name for draft block basepoints.
3729 * @param type type of the label.
3730 * @param reservedName reversed point name. Use when need reserve name, but point is not in data base yet.
3731 * @return unique name for current draft block.
3732 */
3733QString VPattern::GenerateLabel(const LabelType &type, const QString &reservedName) const
3734{
3735 if (type == LabelType::NewPatternPiece)
3736 {
3737 const QDomNodeList blockList = elementsByTagName(TagDraftBlock);
3738 QString name;
3739 int i = 0;
3740 for (;;)
3741 {
3742 name = GetLabelBase(static_cast<quint32>(blockList.size() + i));
3743 if (data->IsUnique(name))
3744 {
3745 return name;
3746 }
3747 if (i == INT_MAX)
3748 {
3749 break;
3750 }
3751 ++i;
3752 }
3753 qCDebug(vXML, "Point name: %s", qUtf8Printable(name));
3754 return name;
3755 }
3756 else if (type == LabelType::NewLabel)
3757 {
3758 QString labelBase = defaultBasePoint;
3759 if (defaultBasePoint.isEmpty())
3760 {
3761 labelBase = GetLabelBase(static_cast<quint32>(getActiveDraftBlockIndex()));
3762 }
3763
3764 qint32 num = 1;
3765 QString name;
3766 do
3767 {
3768 name = QString("%1%2").arg(labelBase).arg(num);
3769 num++;
3770 if (num == INT_MAX)
3771 {
3772 break;
3773 }
3774 } while (data->IsUnique(name) == false || name == reservedName);
3775 qCDebug(vXML, "Point name: %s", qUtf8Printable(name));
3776 return name;
3777 }
3778 qCDebug(vXML, "Got unknown type %d", static_cast<int>(type));
3779 return QString();
3780}

3786 const QStringList uniqueNames = VContainer::AllUniqueNames();
3787 qint32 num = 1;
3788 QString suffix;
3789 for (;;)
3790 {
3791 suffix = QString("_%1%2%3").arg(suffixBase).arg(num).arg(type);
3792

3794 {
3795 if (not data->IsUnique(uniqueNames.at(i) + suffix))
3796 {
3797 break;
3798 }
3799
3800 if (i == uniqueNames.size()-1)
3801 {
3802 qCDebug(vXML, "Suffix is: %s", qUtf8Printable(suffix));
3803 return suffix;

3805 }
3806
3807 if (num == INT_MAX)
3808 {
3809 break;
3810 }
3811 ++num;

4063//---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4064QT_WARNING_PUSH
4065QT_WARNING_DISABLE_GCC("-Wswitch-default")
4066
4067QRectF VPattern::ActiveDrawBoundingRect() const
4068{
4069 // This check helps to find missed tools in the switch
4070 Q_STATIC_ASSERT_X(static_cast<int>(Tool::LAST_ONE_DO_NOT_USE) == 54, "Not all tools were used.");
4071
4072 QRectF rect;
4073
4074 for (qint32 i = 0; i< history.size(); ++i)
4075 {
4076 const VToolRecord tool = history.at(i);
4077 if (tool.getDraftBlockName() == activeDraftBlock)
4078 {
4079 switch ( tool.getTypeTool() )
4080 {
4081 case Tool::Arrow:
4082 case Tool::SinglePoint:
4083 case Tool::DoublePoint:
4084 case Tool::LinePoint:
4085 case Tool::AbstractSpline:
4086 case Tool::Cut:
4087 case Tool::Midpoint:// Same as Tool::AlongLine, but tool will never has such type
4088 case Tool::ArcIntersectAxis:// Same as Tool::CurveIntersectAxis, but tool will never has such type
4089 case Tool::BackgroundImage:
4090 case Tool::LAST_ONE_DO_NOT_USE:
4091 Q_UNREACHABLE();
4092 break;
4093 case Tool::BasePoint:
4094 case Tool::LineIntersect:
4095 case Tool::PointOfContact:
4096 case Tool::Triangle:
4097 case Tool::PointOfIntersection:
4098 case Tool::CutArc:
4099 case Tool::CutSpline:
4100 case Tool::CutSplinePath:
4101 case Tool::PointOfIntersectionArcs:
4102 case Tool::PointOfIntersectionCircles:
4103 case Tool::PointOfIntersectionCurves:
4104 case Tool::PointFromCircleAndTangent:
4105 case Tool::PointFromArcAndTangent:
4106 rect = ToolBoundingRect<VToolSinglePoint>(rect, tool.getId());
4107 break;
4108 case Tool::EndLine:
4109 case Tool::AlongLine:
4110 case Tool::ShoulderPoint:
4111 case Tool::Normal:
4112 case Tool::Bisector:
4113 case Tool::Height:
4114 case Tool::LineIntersectAxis:
4115 case Tool::CurveIntersectAxis:
4116 rect = ToolBoundingRect<VToolLinePoint>(rect, tool.getId());
4117 break;
4118 case Tool::Line:
4119 rect = ToolBoundingRect<VToolLine>(rect, tool.getId());
4120 break;
4121 case Tool::Spline:
4122 case Tool::CubicBezier:
4123 case Tool::Arc:
4124 case Tool::SplinePath:
4125 case Tool::CubicBezierPath:
4126 case Tool::ArcWithLength:
4127 case Tool::EllipticalArc:
4128 rect = ToolBoundingRect<VAbstractSpline>(rect, tool.getId());
4129 break;
4130 case Tool::TrueDarts:
4131 rect = ToolBoundingRect<VToolDoublePoint>(rect, tool.getId());
4132 break;
4133 case Tool::Rotation:
4134 case Tool::MirrorByLine:
4135 case Tool::MirrorByAxis:
4136 case Tool::Move:
4137 rect = ToolBoundingRect<VAbstractOperation>(rect, tool.getId());
4138 break;
4139 //These tools are not accesseble in Draw mode, but still 'history' contains them.
4140 case Tool::Piece:
4141 case Tool::Union:
4142 case Tool::NodeArc:
4143 case Tool::NodeElArc:
4144 case Tool::NodePoint:
4145 case Tool::NodeSpline:
4146 case Tool::NodeSplinePath:
4147 case Tool::Group:
4148 case Tool::InternalPath:
4149 case Tool::AnchorPoint:
4150 case Tool::InsertNodes:
4151 break;
4152 }
4153 }
4154 }
4155 return rect;
4156}

4160//---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4161template <typename T>
4162QRectF VPattern::ToolBoundingRect(const QRectF &rect, const quint32 &id) const
4163{
4164 QRectF toolRect = rect;
4165 if (tools.contains(id))
4166 {
4167 const T *vTool = qobject_cast<T *>(tools.value(id));
4168 SCASSERT(vTool != nullptr)
4169
4170 QRectF childrenRect = vTool->childrenBoundingRect();
4171 //map to scene coordinate.
4172 childrenRect.translate(vTool->scenePos());
4173
4174 toolRect = toolRect.united(vTool->sceneBoundingRect());
4175 toolRect = toolRect.united(childrenRect);
4176 }
4177 else
4178 {
4179 qWarning() << "Can't find tool with id=" << id;
4180 }
4181 return toolRect;
4182}
